N23812976.label: POLITICAL AFAIRS & RELATIONS: MILITARY OPERATIONS Use for declared or undeclared warfare involving two or more nations, i.e., that in which different nations attack one another, eros s boundaries, etc., and for civil war and other kinds of armed conflict which are limited to within a single country, such as restoration of law and order, and protection of the civil population. Includes use of military forces as a deterrent or to exert political pressure, even though such forces are not engaged in combat.

N23812978.label: POL 30 BRAZ 1/1/64
N23812978.raw_scope: Use for materials on defector and expellee matters in general, such as asylum policy, and for materials on individuals in or from host country, usually of importance or prominence in political, professional, or private life, who have been forced to leave or who voluntarily leave their native country because of their political views. Includes departure and arrival, request for and refusal or granting of asylum, and their political activities in behalf of their native country while in exile. Subdivide by name of individual if volume warrants. For refugees as a social problem, SEE: REF outline; for visa matters concerning refugees and escapees, SEE: V outline.
N23812978.scope_stoppers: Use for materials on defector and expellee matters in general, such as asylum policy, and for materials on individuals in or from host country, usually of importance or prominence in political, professional, or private life, who have been forced to leave or who voluntarily leave their native country because of their political views. Includes departure and arrival, request for and refusal or granting of asylum, and their political activities in behalf of their native country while in exile.

N23812859.label: POLITICAL AFAIRS & RELATIONS: MILITARY OPERATIONS Use for declared or undeclared warfare involving two or more nations, i.e., that in which different nations attack one another, eros s boundaries, etc., and for civil war and other kinds of armed conflict which are limited to within a single country, such as restoration of law and order, and protection of the civil population. N23812860.label: POLITICAL AFAIRS & RELATIONS: DEFECTORS & EXPELLEES Use for materials on defector and expellee matters in general, such as asylum policy, and for materials on individuals in or from host country, usually of importance or prominence in political, professional, or private life, who have been forced to leave or who voluntarily leave their native country because of their political views. Includes departure and arrival, request for and refusal or granting of asylum, and their political activities in behalf of their native country while in exile.
